Why do UX researches?

   Diversity of UX methodologies

Diversity

   Choose from our 4 different methodologies

   Each methodology we propose is totally different. You must start by
   establishing your goals and what you really want to learn from the
   study. Let us help you choose between our 4 different research
   methodologies (1to1 interview, user crowdtesting, focus group and
   quantitative survey).
   Rely on our experts

Quality

   Trust our experts for the job

   Our Customer Succes Manager team will help you succed in your studies.
   They are her to answer your questions and assure your test protocol is
   optimised. Each study form it's launch to it's restitution is our core
   business.
   Quick research

Speed

   Get feedback in 5 to 15 days

   You have no time to waste, and your project launch or website /
   application redesign either. That's why we've reduced the time
   production of a remote user test to 7 days.
   Simple interface

Simplicity

   Launch your test in a few clicks

   As you have nothing to install, you can have all your digital or
   physical touch points tested: website, mobile application, connected
   terminals, chatbot, stores, customer service ...
   Agile methods

Agility

   Recover your results on our online platform

   In our agile rendering interface, you can view raw verbatim, filter by
   page and / or category, but also consult the statistics and our summary
   report.
   Autonomous client

Autonomy

   Have the possibility to manage your studies yourself

   Our platform is so intuitive that some of our customers manage verbatim
   analysis themselves, as well as the creation of a new study (remote
   tests only).
   Cutomized client support

Customer Support

   Be advised by our experts

   Your dedicated Ferpection Consultant can also take care of the analysis
   of the verbatim, their synthesis, the UX recommendations, the
   production of a complete report, and if necessary the creation of
   models illustrating its proposals of optimization of your site / app.
   Priorise your redesign roadmap

Prioritisation

   Target what is essential to your clients

   Listening to your prospects and customers, understanding the main
   problems they face on your website, will help you prioritize the
   projects for your development roadmap and your AB testing roadmap.
   Targeting

Targeting

   We help you listen to your core target

   Listen to your B2C, B2B and B2E users in 40 countries through our
   community of 100 000 testers, external recruitment or your own customer
   files.

